# UI Component Library (shadcn/ui)

Lexi uses minimal shadcn/ui components. Only these components exist:

- button.tsx - Button component
- toggle.tsx - Toggle for toolbar buttons
- dialog.tsx - Modal dialogs
- dropdown-menu.tsx - Dropdown menus
- input.tsx - Text input
- label.tsx - Form labels
- separator.tsx - Visual separator

All components use Radix UI primitives with Tailwind CSS styling.

## Component Usage

Always use proper props and accessibility attributes:

```tsx
<Toggle
  pressed={isActive}
  onPressedChange={onClick}
  size="sm"
  variant="outline"
  aria-label="Description"
>
  <Icon />
</Toggle>
```

## Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Follow shadcn/ui patterns
- Maintain consistency with existing components
